write_global_...path_on_clocks(25.10)    write_global_...path_on_clocks(25.10)

Name
       write_global_slack_worst_trigger_path_on_clocks

Syntax
       write_global_slack_worst_trigger_path_on_clocks

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Specifies  whether  the write_global_slack_report command reports worst
       slack on the register  clock  pins  or  not.  When  set  to  true,  the
       write_global_slack_report command reports worst slack due to triggering
       paths.

       A CLK pin might drive a Q pin of the same register, and have a setup or
       hold  check arc with respect to the D pin. In the default setting, when
       the global is set to false, the write_global_slack_report  command  re-
       ports  no slacks along the clock paths. When the global is set to true,
       the command will report the worst slack on register clock pins  due  to
       the related trigger paths and not due to the related timing checks.

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

